  "prompt": "How do I prepare for getting placed in HUL?",
  "response": "To prepare for placement in Hindustan Unilever Limited (HUL), follow these steps:\n\n1. Academic Preparation\n- Maintain a good CGPA\n- Focus on core subjects related to your specialization\n- Develop domain-specific knowledge\n\n2. Technical Skills\n- Understand business fundamentals\n- Learn about FMCG (Fast Moving Consumer Goods) industry\n- Study HUL's product portfolio\n- Know current business trends and challenges\n\n3. Soft Skills Development\n- Improve communication skills\n- Practice public speaking\n- Develop leadership qualities\n- Work on team collaboration\n- Enhance problem-solving abilities\n\n4. Interview Preparation\n- Research HUL's history and culture\n- Understand their recruitment process\n- Practice common interview questions\n- Prepare your resume highlighting achievements\n- Know about HUL's recent initiatives and sustainability efforts\n\n5. Aptitude and HR Preparation\n- Practice quantitative and logical reasoning\n- Learn about behavioral interviewing techniques\n- Develop a strong understanding of your strengths\n- Prepare concise and impactful answers\n\n6. Additional Recommendations\n- Participate in case study competitions\n- Attend company presentations\n- Network with HUL employees\n- Follow HUL's social media and corporate updates\n\n7. Mock Interviews and Group Discussions\n- Participate in mock interviews\n- Practice group discussion skills\n- Get feedback from seniors/mentors",
